  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?** (choose one):\r\n\r\nBUG REPORT\r\n\r\n**Kubernetes version** (use `kubectl version`):\r\n\r\nClient Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"6+\", GitVersion:\"v1.6.0-alpha.0.1499+174305f0a5dacd\", GitCommit:\"174305f0a5dacdbd2687d9133e31d7b1f69cd14a\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", BuildDate:\"2016-12-06T20:09:22Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.7.1\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\nServer Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"6+\", GitVersion:\"v1.6.0-alpha.0.1499+174305f0a5dacd\", GitCommit:\"174305f0a5dacdbd2687d9133e31d7b1f69cd14a\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", BuildDate:\"2016-12-06T20:09:22Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.7.1\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- **Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: AWS\r\n- **OS** (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Any\r\n- **Kernel** (e.g. `uname -a`): Any\r\n- **Install tools**: Any\r\n- **Others**:\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nCreate a pod with a pvc and then try to delete the pvc. This will cause controller to keep trying to delete the volume and fail(Because volume is still attached to the pod). Unlike attach_detach controller which uses exponential backoff, operations in pv_controller run without any sort of backoff. This can potentially cause kubernetes to blow up the API quota of cloud provider pretty quick. \r\n\r\nAlso aforementioned use case is not the only scenario which can cause such inconsistencies, there are several others. \r\n\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nI think, provision and delete operations in `pv_controller` should use a backoff too.  This is narrower use case of - https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/33088#issuecomment-265387940 . CC @jsafrane @childsb @jingxu97 \r\n\r\n\r\nI am working on fixing it. ",
